-- German Exporters Increasingly Concerned About Euro, Currency Wars, FT Says
-- B y   R o n   H a r u i
-- 2010-10-21T00:44:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/german-exporters-increasingly-concerned-about-euro-currency-wars-ft-says.html
Germany’s exporters are expressing
increased concern about the euro’s appreciation against the
dollar and the possibility of a currency war, the Financial
Times  reported .  The newspaper cited several industrialists as saying that
they were worried that export growth may be hurt by a weakening
dollar and the prospect of more credit-easing by the U.S.
Federal Reserve.  To contact the reporter on this story:
